"Were you ringing that bell?"[p]
The woman snorted with a humph.[p]
"I've been expecting you.[p]
It was foretold by Gyromancy."[p]
"What are you talking about?"[p]
"I knew you'd come.[p]
You want the girl, right?"[p]
"The girl? You're talking about Cheryl?"[p]
My eyes grew wide.[p]
"I see everything."[p]
"You know something!? Tell me!"[p]
"Stay back!"[p]
The woman held the palm of her hand out at me, and then lowered her chin[p]
in a way that suggested, "please calm down."[p]
"Nothing is to be gained by floundering about at random.[p]
You must follow the path.[p]
The path of the hermit, concealed by Flauros..."[p]
"What?[p]
What are you talking about?"[p]
I asked once more without hiding my bewilderment.[p]
"Here, the Flauros, a cage of peace.[p]
It can break through the walls of darkness, and counteract the wrath of the underworld.[p]
These will help you.[p]
Make haste to the hospital before it's too late."[p]
The woman held up a strange object and then softly placed it on the desk on top of the altar.[p]
"Wait! Don't go yet!"[p]


